summary: This document appears to be a transcript or summary of a November 26, 2021 call discussing forensic imaging tools and processes, specifically referencing Access Data AD Lab software and evidence items GX 405, 419, 418, 420, 421, 422. It is subject to a protective order and relates to computer forensic examination procedures.

events.title: Forensic Tools Discussion Call
events.description: A call discussing forensic imaging tools and processes, including the use of Access Data AD Lab software and the generation of specific evidence items.

keyFacts: The document records a November 26, 2021 call about forensic imaging tools and procedures.
Evidence items GX 405 and 419 were generated by Access Data AD Lab, a computer forensic program.
Evidence items GX 418, 420, 421, 422 were created under a user profile named 'gmax'.
The document is subject to a protective order covering specific paragraphs (7, 8, 9, 10, 15, and 17).
Discusses validation of forensic tools by a headquarters group before use by CART (Computer Analysis and Response Team).
